3 - VARIABLES

At the start of the code, variables listed out under the umbrella "variables:"
This includes all variables, whether they have assigned data or not
"variables:" must not be indented

4: To assign data to variables, use "is"

5: To show the variable name, use "the" or "The" interchangeably before the variable name. If the variable name is more than one word, underscores"_" are put between the words to merge the words ans one variable name

6: Empty variables have empty quotation marks instead of data for vacancy "" or ''

7: Data assigned to variables are written immediately after "is" and in qoutation marks "" or ''. All in the quotation marks are saved as data. TYXAR can understand variables that contain sectences especially when its hardcoded



8: To assign multiple data to multiple variables, a semi column ";" is used to differenciate between variables.

9: Variables can be written on the same line as the unbrella or the next line, or one variable per line. Indentation is only for neatness here and does not matter.

